title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 20 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has increased over the Year.

Unemployment rate is gradually increasing from 2019 to 2015, roughly constant from 2015 to 2014, slightly increasing from 2014 to 2013, roughly constant from 2013 to 2010, slightly decreasing from 2010 to 2008, roughly constant from 2008 to 2001, and lastly roughly increasing from 2001 to 2000.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2009 and 2008.
Max Unemployment rate about 8.2 was recorded at Year 2010
Min Unemployment rate about 3.6 was recorded at Year 2019
